This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with stereo reconstruction and optical flow, which are both subfields of computer vision. The paper also proposes a method that learns the matching function, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of contextual features, which is a common technique in robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
